channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Draw Your Art Dream: Diverse Digital Art Synthesis with Multimodal Guided Diffusion
item.description: Extensive experimental results on the quality and quantity of the generated digital art paintings confirm the effectiveness of the combination of the diffusion model and multimodal guidance.

item.title: Assessing Digital Language Support on a Global Scale
item.description: The users of endangered languages struggle to thrive in a digitally-mediated world.

item.title: Neural Network Panning: Screening the Optimal Sparse Network Before Training
item.description: Pruning on neural networks before training not only compresses the original models, but also accelerates the network training phase, which has substantial application value.

item.title: Collaborative Decision Making Using Action Suggestions
item.description: The assumption of a collaborative environment enables us to use the agent's policy to estimate the distribution over action suggestions.

item.title: Simultaneous Acquisition of High Quality RGB Image and Polarization Information using a Sparse Polarization Sensor
item.description: Our proposed network architecture consists of an RGB image refinement network and a polarization information compensation network.

item.title: Embracing Consistency: A One-Stage Approach for Spatio-Temporal Video Grounding
item.description: Spatio-Temporal video grounding (STVG) focuses on retrieving the spatio-temporal tube of a specific object depicted by a free-form textual expression.

item.title: Semi-Blind Source Separation with Learned Constraints
item.description: BSS problems being ill-posed, the resolution requires efficient regularization schemes to better distinguish between the sources and yield interpretable solutions.

item.title: Learning State-Aware Visual Representations from Audible Interactions
item.description: However, learning representations from videos can be challenging.

item.title: Formal Conceptual Views in Neural Networks
item.description: Explaining neural network models is a challenging task that remains unsolved in its entirety to this day.

item.title: Learning-Based Dimensionality Reduction for Computing Compact and Effective Local Feature Descriptors
item.description: A distinctive representation of image patches in form of features is a key component of many computer vision and robotics tasks, such as image matching, image retrieval, and visual localization.

item.title: Optimization of Annealed Importance Sampling Hyperparameters
item.description: Annealed Importance Sampling (AIS) is a popular algorithm used to estimates the intractable marginal likelihood of deep generative models.

item.title: Outlier Suppression: Pushing the Limit of Low-bit Transformer Language Models
item.description: With the trends of large NLP models, the increasing memory and computation costs hinder their efficient deployment on resource-limited devices.

item.title: Biologically-Plausible Determinant Maximization Neural Networks for Blind Separation of Correlated Sources
item.description: Previous work on biologically-plausible BSS algorithms assumed that observed signals are linear mixtures of statistically independent or uncorrelated sources, limiting the domain of applicability of these algorithms.

item.title: Learning to Counter: Stochastic Feature-based Learning for Diverse Counterfactual Explanations
item.description: Interpretable machine learning seeks to understand the reasoning process of complex black-box systems that are long notorious for lack of explainability.

item.title: A Novel Dataset for Evaluating and Alleviating Domain Shift for Human Detection in Agricultural Fields
item.description: In this paper we evaluate the impact of domain shift on human detection models trained on well known object detection datasets when deployed on data outside the distribution of the training set, as well as propose methods to alleviate such phenomena based on the available annotations from the target domain.

item.title: Exploiting Transformer in Reinforcement Learning for Interpretable Temporal Logic Motion Planning
item.description: Automaton based approaches have enabled robots to perform various complex tasks.

item.title: Motion Transformer with Global Intention Localization and Local Movement Refinement
item.description: Experiments show that MTR achieves state-of-the-art performance on both the marginal and joint motion prediction challenges, ranking 1st on the leaderboards of Waymo Open Motion Dataset.

item.title: EditEval: An Instruction-Based Benchmark for Text Improvements
item.description: Evaluation of text generation to date has primarily focused on content created sequentially, rather than improvements on a piece of text.

item.title: Im2Oil: Stroke-Based Oil Painting Rendering with Linearly Controllable Fineness Via Adaptive Sampling
item.description: Comparison with existing state-of-the-art oil painting techniques shows that our results have higher fidelity and more realistic textures.

item.title: OBBStacking: An Ensemble Method for Remote Sensing Object Detection
item.description: Trying to address these problems, this paper proposes OBBStacking, an ensemble method that is compatible with OBBs and combines the detection results in a learned fashion.

item.title: StyleMask: Disentangling the Style Space of StyleGAN2 for Neural Face Reenactment
item.description: In this paper we address the problem of neural face reenactment, where, given a pair of a source and a target facial image, we need to transfer the target's pose (defined as the head pose and its facial expressions) to the source image, by preserving at the same time the source's identity characteristics (e. g., facial shape, hair style, etc), even in the challenging case where the source and the target faces belong to different identities.

item.title: SuperYOLO: Super Resolution Assisted Object Detection in Multimodal Remote Sensing Imagery
item.description: In this paper, we propose an accurate yet fast small object detection method for RSI, named SuperYOLO, which fuses multimodal data and performs high resolution (HR) object detection on multiscale objects by utilizing the assisted super resolution (SR) learning and considering both the detection accuracy and computation cost.

item.title: Exploring the Algorithm-Dependent Generalization of AUPRC Optimization with List Stability
item.description: Stochastic optimization of the Area Under the Precision-Recall Curve (AUPRC) is a crucial problem for machine learning.

item.title: Globally Optimal Event-Based Divergence Estimation for Ventral Landing
item.description: This is achieved by estimating divergence (inverse TTC), which is the rate of radial optic flow, from the event stream generated during landing.

item.title: Predicting Affective Vocal Bursts with Finetuned wav2vec 2.0
item.description: The studies of predicting affective states from human voices have relied heavily on speech.

item.title: CrossDTR: Cross-view and Depth-guided Transformers for 3D Object Detection
item.description: To achieve accurate 3D object detection at a low cost for autonomous driving, many multi-camera methods have been proposed and solved the occlusion problem of monocular approaches.

item.title: WeightedSHAP: analyzing and improving Shapley based feature attributions
item.description: On several real-world datasets, we demonstrate that the influential features identified by WeightedSHAP are better able to recapitulate the model's predictions compared to the features identified by the Shapley value.

item.title: Scaling Laws For Deep Learning Based Image Reconstruction
item.description: Current methods are only trained on a few hundreds or thousands of images as opposed to the millions of examples deep networks are trained on in other domains.

item.title: FreeSeg: Free Mask from Interpretable Contrastive Language-Image Pretraining for Semantic Segmentation
item.description: We call the proposed framework as FreeSeg, where the mask is freely available from raw feature map of pretraining model.

item.title: IdeaReader: A Machine Reading System for Understanding the Idea Flow of Scientific Publications
item.description: Understanding the origin and influence of the publication's idea is critical to conducting scientific research.

item.title: Sauron U-Net: Simple automated redundancy elimination in medical image segmentation via filter pruning
item.description: We present Sauron, a filter pruning method that eliminates redundant feature maps by discarding the corresponding filters with automatically-adjusted layer-specific thresholds.

item.title: WikiDes: A Wikipedia-Based Dataset for Generating Short Descriptions from Paragraphs
item.description: In this paper, we introduce WikiDes, a novel dataset to generate short descriptions of Wikipedia articles for the problem of text summarization.

item.title: EPIC-KITCHENS VISOR Benchmark: VIdeo Segmentations and Object Relations
item.description: VISOR annotates videos from EPIC-KITCHENS, which comes with a new set of challenges not encountered in current video segmentation datasets.

item.title: Prayatul Matrix: A Direct Comparison Approach to Evaluate Performance of Supervised Machine Learning Models
item.description: In this paper, an alternative approach is proposed for direct comparison of supervised ML models in terms of individual instances within the dataset.

item.title: Generalized Parametric Contrastive Learning
item.description: Based on theoretical analysis, we observe that supervised contrastive loss tends to bias high-frequency classes and thus increases the difficulty of imbalanced learning.

item.title: Training Efficient Controllers via Analytic Policy Gradient
item.description: Conversely, learning-based offline optimization approaches, such as Reinforcement Learning (RL), allow fast and efficient execution on the robot but hardly match the accuracy of MPC in trajectory tracking tasks.

item.title: Where2comm: Communication-Efficient Collaborative Perception via Spatial Confidence Maps
item.description: Where2comm has two distinct advantages: i) it considers pragmatic compression and uses less communication to achieve higher perception performance by focusing on perceptually critical areas; and ii) it can handle varying communication bandwidth by dynamically adjusting spatial areas involved in communication.

item.title: Device-friendly Guava fruit and leaf disease detection using deep learning
item.description: This work presents a deep learning-based plant disease diagnostic system using images of fruits and leaves.

item.title: Rethinking Motion Deblurring Training: A Segmentation-Based Method for Simulating Non-Uniform Motion Blurred Images
item.description: Successful training of end-to-end deep networks for real motion deblurring requires datasets of sharp/blurred image pairs that are realistic and diverse enough to achieve generalization to real blurred images.

item.title: Text Summarization with Oracle Expectation
item.description: Extractive summarization produces summaries by identifying and concatenating the most important sentences in a document.

item.title: Rethinking Resolution in the Context of Efficient Video Recognition
item.description: Our key finding is that the major cause of degradation is not information loss in the down-sampling process, but rather the mismatch between network architecture and input scale.

item.title: TAD: A Large-Scale Benchmark for Traffic Accidents Detection from Video Surveillance
item.description: After integration and annotation by various dimensions, a large-scale traffic accidents dataset named TAD is proposed in this work.

item.title: An Explainable Machine Learning Approach to Visual-Interactive Labeling: A Case Study on Non-communicable Disease Data
item.description: We demonstrate that EBM is an excellent choice of predictive model by comparing it against a rule-based and four other machine learning models.

item.title: Multi-dataset Training of Transformers for Robust Action Recognition
item.description: We study the task of robust feature representations, aiming to generalize well on multiple datasets for action recognition.

item.title: Multi-stage image denoising with the wavelet transform
item.description: Deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) are used for image denoising via automatically mining accurate structure information.

item.title: Learning to Learn with Generative Models of Neural Network Checkpoints
item.description: We explore a data-driven approach for learning to optimize neural networks.

item.title: Model Predictive Monitoring of Dynamic Systems for Signal Temporal Logic Specifications
item.description: To this end, effective approaches for the computation of feasible sets of STL formulae are provided.

item.title: Out-of-Distribution Detection with Hilbert-Schmidt Independence Optimization
item.description: Existing works attempt to solve the problem by explicitly imposing uncertainty on classifiers when OOD inputs are exposed to the classifier during training.

item.title: Legal Case Document Similarity: You Need Both Network and Text
item.description: Our experiments establish that our proposed network-based methods significantly improve the correlation with domain experts' opinion when compared to the existing methods for network-based legal document similarity.

item.title: FORESEE: Model-based Reinforcement Learning using Unscented Transform with application to Tuning of Control Barrier Functions
item.description: Our method, depending on the number of sigma points employed, can propagate either mean and covariance with minimal points, or higher-order moments with more points similarly to Monte Carlo.
